<br />
Disasterpiece by Christoffer Dahlby  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This deck should go second. To be sure to go second you bid 4-5 burdens which you can remove with Pippin and Sam later. The Fellowship should move nice and easy not speeding throug the sites. The Hobbits have very powerful stealth cards and Power According to His Stature doesnt make it worse. Merry is just a faboulus card. I will try to attach a Hobbit Sword on him as fast as I can. Then to exert him twice and give his strenght to another companion is just wonderful. My Boromirs will eventually see play very fast. But I wont play it before site 2. The very fast Moria Culture cycles throug my deck and therefore Boromir will be easier to find. The Shadow side is very fast. My hand should be empty after a shadow phase. They Are Coming is such a great card. I play 1 copy of special minions which only should see play when I need them. that makes the suitable for discarding. I can discard them to later play them from discard pile with Host of Thousands or They Are coming. And my Bibos takes up shire cards form the discard pile which is just wonderful.<br />
<br />
